Package: chd2iso-fuse
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Recommends: systemd
Description: FUSE filesystem to expose CHD images as ISO/BIN (PS2-friendly)
 chd2iso-fuse mounts a directory of .chd files and presents read-only .iso
 (2048-byte sectors) or .bin (Mode2/Form2 2324-byte sectors, when enabled)
 on-the-fly. This is useful for PS2 OPL (over SMB/UDPBD) and conserving disk
 space on a NAS by storing compressed CHDs while presenting ISO views.
 .
 Features:
  * DVD/2048 passthrough and CD/2352 â†’ 2048/2324 payload extraction
  * Optional exposure of Mode2/Form2 tracks
  * LRU frame cache with size/entry caps
  * Read-only FUSE filesystem, PS2-friendly

